<h2 id="best-practices-for-data-teams">Best Practices for Data
Teams</h2>
<ul>
<li>Never test with live production data. Create small, representative
datasets (fixtures) that capture edge cases</li>
<li>Mocking is replacing a real component (like a database or an API
call) with a controlled object that returns a predefined result.</li>
<li>All tests should be run automatically every time code is committed
or a merge request is made (Continuous Integration). This is how errors
are caught before they reach the production environment.</li>
<li>Aim for high test coverage, particularly for data transformation
logic and model pre-processing steps. Use tools like pytest-cov to
measure which lines of code are executed during your tests.</li>
</ul>
