<h2 id="hybrid-testing-mocking-an-api-within-an-integration-test">Hybrid
Testing: Mocking an API within an Integration Test</h2>
<p><em>Scenario</em>: We have a data pipeline that:</p>
<ul>
<li>Reads: Data from a local file containing user IDs and raw
scores.</li>
<li>Enriches: Calls a slow external User Status API for each ID to get
the current status ('Active', 'Inactive'). (The part we will mock)</li>
<li>Transforms: Processes the data (e.g., filters out inactive
users).</li>
<li>Writes: Saves the final, enriched data to a local output file.</li>
</ul>
<p>We want to test components 1, 3, and 4 working together
(integration), while component 2 (the API call) is mocked to prevent
network calls and ensure speed.</p>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb21"><pre
class="sourceCode python"><code class="sourceCode python"><span id="cb21-1"><a href="#cb21-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># pipeline.py</span></span>
<span id="cb21-2"><a href="#cb21-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="im">import</span> pandas <span class="im">as</span> pd</span>
<span id="cb21-3"><a href="#cb21-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="im">import</span> requests</span>
<span id="cb21-4"><a href="#cb21-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb21-5"><a href="#cb21-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>EXTERNAL_API_URL <span class="op">=</span> <span class="st">&#39;http://api.external.com/user_status/&#39;</span></span>
<span id="cb21-6"><a href="#cb21-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb21-7"><a href="#cb21-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="kw">def</span> get_user_status_from_api(user_id):</span>
<span id="cb21-8"><a href="#cb21-8" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="co">&quot;&quot;&quot;Real function that hits the slow, external API.&quot;&quot;&quot;</span></span>
<span id="cb21-9"><a href="#cb21-9" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="cf">try</span>:</span>
<span id="cb21-10"><a href="#cb21-10" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>        response <span class="op">=</span> requests.get(<span class="ss">f&quot;</span><span class="sc">{</span>EXTERNAL_API_URL<span class="sc">}{</span>user_id<span class="sc">}</span><span class="ss">&quot;</span>, timeout<span class="op">=</span><span class="dv">5</span>)</span>
<span id="cb21-11"><a href="#cb21-11" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>        response.raise_for_status()</span>
<span id="cb21-12"><a href="#cb21-12" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>        <span class="cf">return</span> response.json().get(<span class="st">&#39;status&#39;</span>, <span class="st">&#39;Unknown&#39;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb21-13"><a href="#cb21-13" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="cf">except</span> requests.exceptions.RequestException:</span>
<span id="cb21-14"><a href="#cb21-14" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>        <span class="cf">return</span> <span class="st">&#39;API_Failed&#39;</span> <span class="co"># Handle failure case gracefully</span></span>
<span id="cb21-15"><a href="#cb21-15" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb21-16"><a href="#cb21-16" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="kw">def</span> run_enrichment_pipeline(input_path, output_path):</span>
<span id="cb21-17"><a href="#cb21-17" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="co">&quot;&quot;&quot;The main ETL function integrating API calls.&quot;&quot;&quot;</span></span>
<span id="cb21-18"><a href="#cb21-18" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    </span>
<span id="cb21-19"><a href="#cb21-19" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="co"># 1. READ (Integration Component)</span></span>
<span id="cb21-20"><a href="#cb21-20" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    df <span class="op">=</span> pd.read_csv(input_path)</span>
<span id="cb21-21"><a href="#cb21-21" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    </span>
<span id="cb21-22"><a href="#cb21-22" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="co"># 2. ENRICHMENT (The API Call - THIS IS THE MOCK TARGET)</span></span>
<span id="cb21-23"><a href="#cb21-23" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="co"># Apply the slow function to every row</span></span>
<span id="cb21-24"><a href="#cb21-24" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    df[<span class="st">&#39;Status&#39;</span>] <span class="op">=</span> df[<span class="st">&#39;ID&#39;</span>].<span class="bu">apply</span>(get_user_status_from_api)</span>
<span id="cb21-25"><a href="#cb21-25" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    </span>
<span id="cb21-26"><a href="#cb21-26" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="co"># 3. TRANSFORMATION (Integration Component)</span></span>
<span id="cb21-27"><a href="#cb21-27" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="co"># Filter out inactive users and API failures</span></span>
<span id="cb21-28"><a href="#cb21-28" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    df_filtered <span class="op">=</span> df[df[<span class="st">&#39;Status&#39;</span>] <span class="op">==</span> <span class="st">&#39;Active&#39;</span>]</span>
<span id="cb21-29"><a href="#cb21-29" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    </span>
<span id="cb21-30"><a href="#cb21-30" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="co"># 4. WRITE (Integration Component)</span></span>
<span id="cb21-31"><a href="#cb21-31" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    df_filtered.to_csv(output_path, index<span class="op">=</span><span class="va">False</span>)</span></code></pre></div>
